 &HT;    A sweet mess
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _
</P>
<P>
   www.scoreone.com/ _ Spend some time this summer making a mess in
the kitchen and baking some goodies in the process. Choose from
literally hundreds of recipes _ divided into three categories:
``Major Messes,'' ``Sweet and Sticky'' and ``Munchies'' _ submitted
by kids like Elise Griffin, 14, who offers ``Strawberry Mint Face
Mask.'' It's made up of five strawberries, mint leaves, lemon juice
and powdered milk all thrown in a blender. Most are simple recipes
that take just a few minutes to make. Just be sure to clean up your
mess! And don't forget to share your own favorite recipes through
the site's submission form. There's also a bulletin board for
trading recipes and cooking tips and meeting other young, budding
chefs.
</P>
<P>
   www.p2kthemovie.com _ Can't wait for ``Pokemon 2000, The Movie''
to come out on July 21? Whet your appetite for Pokemon at this
official movie Web site. Listen to songs from the soundtrack, watch
movie trailers and see a bonus mini-movie, ``Pikachu's Rescue
(backslash)Adventure.'' Check out Pokedex, Pokematch and a pop quiz
to test your Pokemon knowledge.
</P>
