<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Here's how to juggle like a pro!
 &HT;    By Ryon Horne
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ It's all in the imaginary square.
</P>
<P>
   That's what Ron Anglin would say if you were in his juggling
workshop at the Horizons Circus Camp. He was kind enough to share
with readers the basics of ``cascade juggling.''
</P>
<P>
   For starters, he suggested that you:
</P>
<P>
   1. Practice in front of your bed so the objects you drop will
fall in front of you.
</P>
<P>
   2. Start by using plastic grocery bags in which you've torn a
small hole in the bottoms. You'll learn the movements easily
because the bags move through the air slowly. Once you get the hang
of it, you'll be able to juggle with balls and other objects.
</P>
<P>
   Let's learn how to juggle!
</P>
<P>
   JUGGLING WITH TWO BAGS
</P>
<P>
   _ Imagine there's a square in front of you.
</P>
<P>
   _ Hold the end of one bag in your right hand and toss it to the
top left corner of the imaginary square. (Lift very hard when you
toss.)
</P>
<P>
   _ Toss your second bag _ the one in your left hand _ to the top
right corner of the imaginary square.
</P>
<P>
   _ Catch the bag on the left with your left hand. Catch the bag
on the right with your right hand.
</P>
<P>
   _ Do this until you are comfortable juggling with both hands.
</P>
<P>
   JUGGLING WITH THREE BAGS
</P>
<P>
   _ In your right hand, hold one bag between the pointer and
middle fingers while holding another one between your thumb and the
other fingers. In your left hand, hold the third bag.
</P>
<P>
   _ Toss the bag held between the pointer and middle fingers _
aiming for the top left corner. (See top photo.)
</P>
<P>
   _ Then toss the bag in your left hand to the top right corner
and catch the first bag with your left hand. (See second photo.)
</P>
<P>
   _ Toss the third bag across to the top left corner and catch the
second bag with your right hand. (See third photo.)
</P>
<P>
   _ Keep going. You'll always have one bag in the air and one in
each hand.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-07-03-00 1153EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
