<P>
   These feature stories are moving today to clients of the New
York Times News Service. Stories are for release Tuesday, July 4
and Wednesday, July 5, 2000, unless otherwise embargoed.
</P>
<P>
   TECHNOLOGY
</P>
<P>
   COXNET PTECH PAGE
</P>
<P>
   EDs: This is the CoxNet PTECH page for the current week. This
layout is available Tuesday after 2 p.m. EDT.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET PTECH 0704 _ Your high-speed Internet connection could
make you vulnerable to even casual hackers prying into e-mail and
private data on your computer's hard drive. (Tamman, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) Art includes a 3-column color illustration of
a man working on a computer, while thieves pry open the back.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   LIST BOX _ A list of ways computers can be attacked.
</P>
<P>
   TECHNOBUDDY _ Upon further review, the merits of the MP3 musical
format become obvious. (Husted, Atlanta Journal-Constitution.) Art
includes 1 column color sig of columnist.
</P>
<P>
   GADGETS _ New, innovative headphones from Bose cancel out
unwanted noise. (Cummings, Dayton Daily News) Art includes a
18-pica color photo of a man wearing the headphones.
</P>
<P>
   TECH TOOLS _ A new e-mail service offers up worldly pearls of
wisdom. (Husted, Atlanta Journal-Constitution.)
</P>
<P>
   GAME CORNER _ Street Fighter Alpha 3 offers up more fast,
furious fun. (Staff, Austin American-Statesman) Art includes a
6-pica color photo of the box of Street Fighter Alpha 3.
</P>
<P>
   GADGETS-PRINTER _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Canon has introduced a printer
designed for people who use set-top boxes, such as Microsoft's
WebTV, to browse the Internet via their televisions. (Cummings,
Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TECH-PLAYGEAR _ The latest in digital game gear. This week: The
Personal Cooling System 2.0. (Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TECH-HOMEGEAR _ The latest in digital home gear. This week: The
``Original'' Grill Pad (Austin American-Statesman). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TECH-KIDGEAR _ Games for children. This week: I See Sue . . .
the T.rex. (Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TECH-WEEWEB _ Websites for children. This week: Recipes on the
Web. (Austin American-Statesman). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TECH-CENTERPIECE _ Weekly centerpiece on personal technology,
from products to trends to advancements. This week: getting rid of
PC fears. (Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). MOVED
</P>
<P>
   with
</P>
<P>
   TECH-SIDE _ Advice for newcomers to computers and the Internet.
(Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). MOVED
</P>
<P>
   TECHNOBUDDY_ Popular column about personal computing written for
the average user. This week: digital cameras, recordable CDs and
UPS. (Husted, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TECH-TOOLS _ Software reviews. This week: Ontrack's SystemSuite
2000. (Warner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   NETWATCH _ What's new on the Web. This week: downloading digital
music. (Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TECH-SAVVY _ Question and answer column focusing on using
computers and other technology as tools to get jobs done.
(Cleere/Rudd, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   JULY4-CONSUMERS _ What better day to promote independence than
July 4? The steps we take toward our own independence are
significant _ whether we're an infant rolling over for the first
time, a teen coping with disability, a widow or widower rebuilding
our lives after the loss of a spouse. Fortunately, there are
products and services designed to foster independence at every age
and every stage of our lives. We've assembled a few in honor of the
holiday. (Dayton Daily News). 33. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   CONSUMERQ&AMP;A _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Consumer Q&AMP;A. (Greig, Austin
American-Statesman) (l, a) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   PSYCHOLOGY-LECRONE _ Dr. Hap LeCrone's weekly psychology column.
This week: (LeCrone, Waco Tribune-Herald) EMBARGOED FOR WEDNESDAY
</P>
<P>
   SCIENCE-MEDICINE
</P>
<P>
   AUTISM _ ATLANTA _ Aside from Hollywood's sometimes inaccurate
portrayal of autism, few people know much about the disorder. A
gathering this week in Atlanta sponsored by the Autism Society of
America, ``2000 National Conference On Autism: Celebrating Our
Future,'' is focusing teatment options, research and incidence of
autism. The conference continues through Wednesday at the Downtown
Hilton Hotel. (Anthony, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   MEDICAL-LEGENDS _Bananas tained with flesh-eating bacteria.
HIV-infected needles left in movie theater seats. People awaking in
bathtubs of ice to find their kidneys removed. If you have e-mail,
chances are you've received notes about these and dozens of other
alleged health hazards - sometimes frightening, sometimes humorous,
and always untrue. Driven by the Interne, health-related ``urban
legends'' are creating misinformation on such a national scale that
the CDC recently created a website dedicated to knocking them down.
So why are we interested and how can you know if what you hear is
true? With cool ``Tales from the Crypt''-style illustration and
list of the top 15 most common. (Kicklighter, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 40.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   MEDICAL-LEGENDS-LIST _ List of web sites and books on urban
legends.(Kicklighter, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 7.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS
</P>
<P>
   HOLLOWAY-TVCOLUMN _ Observations on the television industry from
a leading commentator. This week: ``Big Brother.'' (Holloway,
Austin American-Statesman). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   NEWSSTAND _ Periodicals on the newsstands this week. (O'Briant,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   NEWS FOR KIDS
</P>
<P>
   NFK-CHECKITOUT _ A brief on a new web site, TV show or event for
kids. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   NFK-NEWSFLASH _ Three or four briefs of world and national news,
written for kids to understand. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   NFK-FEATURE _ A feature about a celebrity kid, kid's event, or
big news story explained for kids, for papers' kids or family
pages. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   AUTOMOTIVE NEWS
</P>
<P>
   COXNET WHEELS _ (EDS: This is the CoxNet WHEELS page for the
current week. This layout is available Tuesday by 2 p.m. EDT.)
</P>
<P>
   COXNET WHEELS 0704 -- Although its styling runs ahead of its
performance, the Pontiac Grand Am still offers a balance of
features that makes it the division's best-selling car. (DeVault,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Art includes a 4-column color photo
of the 2000 Pontiac Grand Am SE1 and a 2-column color photo of the
car's interior.
</P>
