<P>
   POLITICAL NEWS (``p'' category)
</P>
<P>
   NADER-SPOILER (Washington) _ The spoiler scenario has been a
recurring theme during this presidential campaign. Earlier,
Republicans were concerned that Patrick Buchanan would erode
conservative support for Texas Gov. George W. Bush. Now Vice
President Al Gore faces a threat from the left _ Green Party
candidate Ralph Nader. But Nader rejects the idea that he could
take enough votes from Gore to ruin the Democrat's chances. ``I
don't view myself as a spoiler, but as a reformer,'' Nader says. By
GARY MARTIN.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ As speculation mounts about
potential running mates for Al Gore and George W. Bush, there's now
a contrarian view: Who needs a vice president anyway? Let's get rid
of that useless appendage! By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
<P>
   For Wednesday:
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ In his dissent from the Supreme
Court ruling that the Boy Scouts may bar gays as troop leaders,
Justice John Paul Stevens quotes the legendary Justice Louis
Brandeis: ``We must be ever on our guard lest we erect our
prejudices into legal principles.'' The majority, who found that
the Scouts could not be forced to accept troop leaders they do not
want, was more worried about the group's freedom of expressive
association. It was a classic conflict of rights, and the high
bench made the wrong pick. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
