<HEADLINE>
EARLIER `RIPLEY' BETTER; WATERS UNDER TNE BRIDGE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``The Talented Mr. Ripley'' (DVD) _ Alain Delon's
stunning performance in ``Purple Noon,'' the 1960 adaptation of
Patricia Highsmith's novel, ``The Talented Mr. Ripley,'' clouds my
feelings about this latest version. Matt Damon's Mr. Ripley is
satisfactory, but his performance isn't as dark and deep as
Delon's. Jude Law should have played the title role instead of the
supporting one.
</P>
<P>
   ``Divine Trash'' (DVD) _ This affectionate, appreciative look at
the films of John Waters also contains a commentary by George
Mansour, a Boston film booker and longtime Waters fan. What's
interesting is that as Waters's movies had commercial success, they
became less offensive. Consequently, his aggressive bad taste has
evolved into more comfortable acceptabilty.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   NEW ON DVD: ``Mr. Death: The Rise and Fall of Fred A. Leuchter
Jr.'' _ When will the nutty awards people finally grant Errol
Morris the respect he deserves? Not soon. This nonfiction film
documents the story of Fred Leuchter Jr., an electric-chair
repairman who also denies the Holocaust. Instead of pushing and
hammering the misguided Lechter into a convenient pigeonhole,
Morris allows his subject the full range of his eccentricity.
That's what makes this film so terrific. Morris doesn't tell us
what to think, he just allows us to share his intellectual
astonishment. And what could be better _ or less likely to win an
Oscar _ than that?
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: July 11: ``The Hurricane'' (DVD), ``All
About My Mother'' (DVD), ``Boiler Room,'' ``My Dog Skip'' (DVD),
``Jaws'' (DVD), ``The Fourth Floor,'' ``Mansfield Park,'' ``Active
Stealth,'' ``The Fourth Floor'' (DVD). July 18: ``Ride With the
Devil,'' ``What Planet Are You From?'' (DVD), ``Identification of a
Woman,'' ``Angela's Ashes,'' ``Diamonds,'' ``Behind Locked Doors,''
``Il Bidone'' (DVD), ``The Ninth Gate,'' ``The War Zone.'' July 25:
``Magnolia'' (DVD), ``The Beach,'' ``The Perfect Tenant,''
``Drowning Mona,'' ``Bruce Brown Surf Collection,'' ``The Secret of
Roan Inish'' (DVD), ``Space Jam'' (DVD). Aug. 1: ``The Brothers
Quay Collection'' (DVD). Aug. 8: ``Reindeer Games,'' ``Holy
Smoke,'' ``The Grandfather.'' Aug. 15: ``It's the Rage,'' ``Ghost
Dog'' (DVD). Aug. 22: ``The Tigger Movie'' (DVD), ``Mifune.''
</P>
</TEXT>
