<HEADER>
A1923 &Cx1f; tic-z
r b BC-ARIZONA-REPUBLIC &LR;      07-03 0331
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ARIZONA-REPUBLIC </SLUG>
  
Three men were found dead in a Tempe apartment early
Saturday.Triple slaying rattles Tempe
<TEXT>
<P>
   Bodies found &QL;
</P>
<P>
   in apartmentThe discovery of three bodies in a Tempe apartment
Saturday touched off an intense investigation and left residents in
this quiet community scared and seeking answers.
</P>
<P>
   Tempe police released little information about the three males
found dead inside an apartment at the Mariner at 1525 E. Baseline
Road, west of McClintock Drive.
</P>
<P>
   The apartment complex abuts the popular and well-maintained
housing community called the Lakes. Residents said the area has a
good reputation.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've never had any problems,'' said Connie Belperio, who
lives at the Mariner. ``We've never had to call the police for
anything.''
</P>
<P>
   Belperio, a five-year resident of the complex, said she knew
nothing about the tragedy in the adjacent building until officers
knocked on her door about 4 a.m. Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was freaked,'' Belperio said. ``I haven't slept since.''
</P>
<P>
   Just before 1 a.m., a woman called police to say there ``were
victims down'' inside the apartment, said Sgt. Wil Price. Police
said the caller learned of the bodies from someone else but would
not go into detail.
</P>
<P>
   Officers pushed open an unlocked door and discovered the bodies.
The door appeared damaged, but officers were unable to say whether
it was related to the killings.
</P>
<P>
   Preble Ware, whose back yard faces the apartment complex, was
grilling hamburgers outside about 8:15p.m. Friday when he heard a
scream. Several seconds later, Ware said, he heard a pop. Then
silence.
</P>
<P>
   ``I didn't think anything of it at the time,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Ware doesn't know whether what he heard was tied to the
killings.
</P>
<P>
   Police did not give an approximate time or motive for the
deaths. They also did not release the names of the victims, but
said they appear to be in their 20s.
</P>
<P>
   $$$
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Reach the reporter at Monica.Davis(a)Arizona &QL;
