<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-03 14:24 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A1924 &Cx1f; tic-z
r b BC-ARIZONA-REPUBLIC &LR;      07-03 0230
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ARIZONA-REPUBLIC </SLUG>
  
Three people died Saturday morning after an 18-wheeler slammed into
a minivan, sending it crashing over a median wall onto eastbound
Interstate 10.3 are killed as 18-wheeler
<TEXT>
<P>
   hits California van on I-10
</P>
<P>
   Three people died Saturday morning after an 18-wheeler slammed
into a minivan, sending it rolling and crashing over a median onto
eastbound Interstate 10.
</P>
<P>
   Two of the van's passengers, a man and woman, were ejected and
died immediately, authorities said. The third person in the van was
flown by helicopter to Maricopa Medical Center, where he died a few
hours later. The driver of the tractor-trailer truck wasn't hurt.
</P>
<P>
   The 9 a.m. rollover accident just south of Firebird Lake snarled
traffic on both sides of I-10 for about two hours, shutting down
the high-speed lanes in both directions, said Kevin Wood, a
Department of Public Safety spokesman. The interstate in that area
has two lanes in each direction.
</P>
<P>
   None of the victims was identified, but the van had California
license plates.
</P>
<P>
   The rig and van were westbound when the truck began moving into
the left lane,
</P>
<P>
   Wood said. The rear of the rig clipped the van's passenger side,
which flipped the van over the median.
</P>
<P>
   The crash was still under investigation.
</P>
<P>
   $$$
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Reach the reporter at Chip.Scutari(a)ArizonaRepublic.com or
(602) 444-7482.
</P>
<P>
   &AMP;lt;/default&AMP;gt;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
