<TEXT>
<P>
   Entertainment and culture stories from The N.Y. Times News
Service for Tuesday, July 4.
</P>
<P>
   LORCA-COLUMBIA (New York) _ This month, Columbia University is
celebrating the centenary of its summer session, and to mark the
occasion it offered a special course on its famous pupil Federico
Garcia Lorca, the Spanish writer whose 10-month stay here resulted
in one of his greatest works, ``Poet in New York.'' By Dinitia
Smith.
</P>
<P>
   With photo, NYT3.
</P>
<P>
   JORDAN-MEMOIR (New Yokr) _ The writer June Jordan revisits her
painful childhood in a new memoir.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   REFUGEES-FILMS (Undated) _ Filmaid International, organized in
just eight weeks, traveled last year to five refugee camps in
Macedonia and assembled open-air movie house to screen movies like
``Titanic,'' ``Mrs. Doubtfire,'' and ``E.T.'' Now an official
project of the International Rescue Committee, which along with the
U.N. High Commissioner for Refugees helped support the project, the
initial funds came from a source not exactly famed for its global
philanthropy: Hollywood. By Jesse McKinley.
</P>
<P>
   BOORSTIN-TV (Undated) _ A Critic's Notebook: Way back in 1961
Daniel Boorstin predicted such television shows as ``Survivors''
and ``Big Brother.'' By Waltert Goodman.
</P>
<P>
   EYRE-OPERA-REVIEW (Cheltenham, England) _ On the world premiere
of an opera based on a classic novel, not one of the Jane Austen
books that might have suited the location, where her characters
would feel right at home, but rather Charlotte Bronte's ``Jane
Eyre.'' Reviewed by Paul Griffiths.
</P>
<P>
   CHILDREN-BOOK-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``What We Don't Know About
Children,'' by Simona Vinci (Knopf). Reviewed by Richard Bernstein.
</P>
<P>
   For information and repeats call the News Service at (888)
346-9867 or (212) 556-1927. And be sure to look for other
entertainment stories from our partners: The Boston Globe, Cox News
Service, Hearst Newspapers, The Houston Chronicle, The Arizona
Republic, Kansas City Star, Fort Worth Star-Telegram, Los Angeles
Daily News, San Francisco Chronicle and Seattle Post-Intelligencer.
</P>
