   TAKING A WARLORD'S ADVICE TO SHAKE UP THE MARKETPLACE
</P>
<P>
   ECOM-JAPAN _ Hiroshi Mikitani's e-ecommerce site, called
Rakuten, has become Japan's largest online bazaar. The site,
www.rakuten.co.jp, draws about 95 million hits a month as a gateway
to about 2,800 merchants around the country selling everything from
eggs to kimonos. Merchants pay 50,000 yen a month, or about $469,
to link their Web sites to Rakuten. In exchange, they receive tips
on jazzing up those sites and access to Rakuten's database and
software, which contain information about customers and their
predilections. Rakuten also offers them low-cost advertising. A
report. By Stephanie Strom.
</P>
