<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MUSIC-FERMAN-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MUZZLING KID ROCK AND OTHER AMUSING MUSICAL NOTES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DAVE FERMAN 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Thoughts, observations and blips on the pop-music radar:
</P>
<P>
   Am I the only one who thinks Kid Rock needs a muzzle? In a
recent Rolling Stone cover story, the Kid notes that he's in a
custody battle for his son Junior with the child's mother, and then
admits to using and selling crack (it's not as bad as most people
think, he says) and dabbling in heroin. Duh. Like that won't be
brought up in court.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Though I admire Sinead O'Connor, she hasn't scored any points
for a) her man-bashing on ``No Man's Woman'' but b) reversing her
field and saying that she actually ``loves blokes'' and doesn't
mean ``man'' in the sense of, you know, ``men.'' Yeah, right,
Sinead, guys are the only ones who make their partners miserable in
relationships. You just keep telling yourself that.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Odd _ and sad _ to see just how little attention was paid to the
death of Johnnie Taylor on May 31. The news of Tito Puente's death
the same day certainly played a part, but that still doesn't
explain how few obituaries and appreciations were on the national
wires that day.
</P>
<P>
   Tito, of course, deserves all the attention and accolades he
got, but Taylor's legacy as one of the great soul men was
definitely given short shrift. If you're interested in learning
more about him, the first place to stop is ``Chronicle _ The 20
Greatest Hits,'' a solid compilation of the many hits he cut for
Stax. Then go back and pick up 1967's ``Wanted: One Soul Singer.''
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   To combat bootleggers, Pearl Jam is recording all 26 of its
summer European shows and will release each as a double CD. The CDs
will be available no later than August at www.pearljam.com and
released in stores later.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Could someone please tell rappers that the old
wave-your-hands-in-the-air-like-you-just-don't-care shtick is over?
And has been for years? Kool Keith and his buddies tried this when
they opened for the Foo Fighters and the Red Hot Chili Peppers a
couple weeks ago, followed by basically every group on the bill,
from Jay-Z on down, doing the same at Summer Jam a couple weeks
back.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   The rapid descents down the charts of the latest CDs by No Doubt
and En Vogue are no surprise. It's amazing that bands can't figure
this out: In an era when that Warholian 15 minutes of fame has been
cut to 10, taking three or four years between CDs is virtual career
suicide. Even when it's actually a good CD, as ``Return to Saturn''
and ``Masterpiece Theatre'' both are. In two years, Gwennie and her
band will be playing Deep Ellum Live in Dallas, which is where they
should have been all along.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Onetime Public Image Ltd. and Ministry drummer Martin Atkins has
formed an industrial supergroup with former or current members of
Ministry, Killing Joke and Pigface, according to the Pollstar Web
site.
</P>
<P>
   The Damage Manual also includes former Ministry vocalist Chris
Connelly, KJ guitarist Geordie Walker and former PiL bassist Jah
Wobble.
</P>
<P>
   The group will record a CD this summer and return with a tour
this fall.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Finally, good news for all fans of Irish music: Karan Casey,
former vocalist for premier Irish/American Celtic band Solas, has
just released ``Seal Maiden: A Celtic Musical,'' a retelling of the
classic Irish fable of a seal turning into a young girl. The CD is
out on the children's label Music for Little People, and it's
wonderful. Contributors read like a who's who of modern Irish
music: Martin Hayes, Dennis Cahill, Iarla O' Lionaird (Afro Celt
Sound System), Niall Vallely (Nomos) and Mairead Ni Mhaonaigh of
Altan.
</P>
<P>
   (Dave Ferman is pop music critic for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. You can call him at (817) 390-7839, or e-mail:
dfer(at)star-telegram.com. Visit the Star-Telegram's online
services on the World Wide Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
