<P>
   MEXICO-ELECTION (Mexico City) _ Ledeall: Vicente Fox, the
president-elect, met with President Ernesto Zedillo on Monday to
discuss Mexico's transition to a new government after Sunday's
election, which shattered the party that has governed Mexico for 70
years and opened the way for a virtual re-creation of the political
system. As Fox fielded congratulatory phone calls from world
leaders, election returns showed that his coattails in Sunday's
balloting helped his center-right party to impressive gains in both
houses of Congress but that no party would win majority control. By
Sam Dillon.
</P>
