<SLUG> BC-PSYCHOLOGY-LECRONE05-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Stress management can cut sports anxiety
 &HT;    By Hap LeCrone
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   His sand wedge descended from its slow, graceful arc and entered
the sand about 2 inches behind the golf ball. With a calculated
explosion of sand, the ball emerged from its resting place and
lifted above the putting surface _ coming to rest a few inches from
the cup. This whole procedure was finely executed in the mind's eye
of the golf professional who was preparing to execute this same
