   BOOKS
</P>
<P>
   SKUBE-COLUMN _ It was inevitable. The marketing phenomenon would
overwhelm the story. Harry Potter was born in children's
imagination as a character, fabulous in the fullest sense. He will
die there as another commodity. (Skube, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
