<P>
   MEXICO-ELECTIONS _ MEXICO CITY _ After a stunning election
victory that toppled the world's longest-governing party, Vicente
Fox on Monday began the process of dismantling the structure that
has ruled Mexico for 71 years. What will change in Mexico, and what
will it mean for the United States? (Ferriss, Cox News Service).
25.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   MEXICO-FOX _ MEXICO CITY _ Vicente Fox, the first opposition
candidate to win Mexico's presidency in more than a century, is a
blunt-talking, cowboy boot-wearing former Coca-Cola executive and
rancher who believes in free markets and has vowed to wipe out
official corruption. A look at this colorful and charismatic
leader. (Ferriss, Cox News Service). 25.
</P>
