<P>
   BUSH-VEEP - Texas Gov. George W. Bush and Dick Cheney, his point
man for running mate selection, meet the press at the Bush ranch
near Waco. (Herman, Austin American-Statesman). 25. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   TEACHERS-NEA _ CHICAGO _ Teachers mourned Barry Grunow of Lake
Worth, Fla., the teacher shot to death on the last day of his class
by a 13-year-old student, at a simultaenous minute of silence at
the opening sessions of the conventions of the National Education
Association here and the American Federation of Teachers in
Philadelphia. (Mollison, Cox News Service). 22.
</P>
<P>
   WAN: Location Atlanta, category National, subcategory Education.
</P>
<P>
   TEACHERSHORTAGE _ As newly hired teachers arrive in Austin _ and
while some key teaching positions remain unfilled _ officials at
AISD are talking about affordable housing. One idea would have the
school pursue deals with landlords, housing subsidies or even
getting the district into the landlord business in order to find
housing for teachers. (Bahadur, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WATERWAR _ For the fourth time since talks began two years ago,
negotiators in the bitter water war between Georgia, Alabama and
Florida must decide whether it's worthwhile to continue
deliberations or abandon the effort and go to court. The states
face an Aug. 1 to come up with an agreement--the fourth such time
limit since the talks kicked off in 1998. Once again, however,
there is little hope that the deadline will be met. (Seabrook,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
