<P>
   JULY4-CONSUMERS _ What better day to promote independence than
July 4? The steps we take toward our own independence are
significant _ whether we're an infant rolling over for the first
time, a teen coping with disability, a widow or widower rebuilding
our lives after the loss of a spouse. Fortunately, there are
products and services designed to foster independence at every age
and every stage of our lives. We've assembled a few in honor of the
holiday. (Dayton Daily News). 33. WITH PHOTOS. MOVED..
</P>
<P>
   CONSUMERQ&AMP;A _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Consumer Q&AMP;A. (Greig, Austin
American-Statesman) (l, a) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   BLACKBEARD _ MOOREHEAD CITY, N.C. _ On the anniversary of
Blackbeard's death, Phil Masters received a phone call he will
never forget. It was Nov. 26, 1996. His company, Intersal, had just
wrapped up a 10-day search for Queen Anne's Revenge. He had
returned to his full-time job in New York the day before. Director
of operations Mike Daniels remained in Beaufort for one last day on
the company's last dime. (Greenville Daily Reflector)
</P>
<P>
   GODS-CHEERLEADERS _ The God Squad. ``2-4, 6-8-10! Who died, who
died for our sins?'' Christian cheerleading camp. (Belkin, Palm
