<P>
   CYC-TOUR _ Belgium's Tom Steels, who rides for the Mapei team,
wins his second consecutive stage in the Tour de France. Lance
Armstrong remains in second place, four seconds back, finishing
with the peloton in the 100.3-mile third stage from Loudun to
Nantes. If all goes right, the U.S. Postal Service team plans to
have Armstrong wearing the overall leader's yellow jersey after
Tuesday's team time trial, a 43.5-mile ride from Nantes to
Saint-Nazaire. The USPS is loaded with good time trial riders, and
everybody on the team gets the same time as the fifth-place rider.
Tuesday's stage is a staggered start with the 20th-place team
starting first. When USPS takes off, it will know what time to
needs to beat. (Halliburton, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   CYC-TOURNOTEBOOK _ Quote de jour, numbers, notes and quotes.
(Halliburton, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
