that politicians and educators should focus more on developing
challenging curriculum and less on testing students. Opening the
American Federation of Teachers biennial convention here Monday
morning, Sandra Feldman, the president, said her members are the
only professionals expected to invent ``their most basic tools''
while practicing their craft, and called for a national consortium
to develop curriculums on all subjects. By Jodi Wilgoren.
