<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SAUCES-RECIPES-LADN-2ndTake </SLUG>
  
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
UNDATED: ... Northland Publishing.
<TEXT>
<P>
   MEDITERRANEAN OLIVE SALSA &QR;
</P>
<P>
   8 ounces Greek OR kalamata olives, pitted and chopped &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1 large tomato, chopped &QR;
</P>
<P>
   4 ounces feta cheese, crumbled &QR;
</P>
<P>
   3 or 4 green onions, chopped &QR;
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons olive oil (or less) &QR;
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons white wine vinegar &QR;
</P>
<P>
   Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl. Serve at room
temperature over grilled beef, fish or chicken. Store in
refrigerator. Makes about 2 1/2 cups. &QL; 
(From ``Chips, Dips &AMP; Salsas,'' by Judy Walker and Kim MacEachern,
Northland Publishing.) &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
ARIZONA CAVIAR &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup red wine vinegar &QR;
</P>
<P>
   2 or 3 cloves garlic, chopped OR minced &QR;
</P>
<P>
   4 teaspoons Tabasco sauce (use more OR less depending on how hot
you like it) &QR;
</P>
<P>
   2 (15-ounce) cans black beans, drained and rinsed &QR;
</P>
<P>
   2 (11-ounce) cans corn, drained and rinsed &QR;
</P>
<P>
   6 tomatoes, chopped &QR;
</P>
<P>
   4 green onions, chopped &QR;
</P>
<P>
   2 avocados, peeled, pitted and chopped (optional) &QR;
</P>
<P>
   Salt and pepper to taste &QR;
</P>
<P>
   Chopped cilantro to taste (we like at least 1/2 cup) &QR;
</P>
<P>
   In a large bowl mix vinegar, garlic and Tabasco. Add remaining
ingredients and mix gently but thoroughly. Refrigerate for a few
hours or overnight, stirring occasionally. Great on grilled steaks,
burgers, chicken or fish. Makes about 5 cups. &QL; 
(From ``Chips, Dips &AMP; Salsas,'' by Judy Walker and Kim MacEachern,
Northland Publishing.) &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
SUN-DRIED TOMATOES AND ROASTED RED PEPPER SAUCE &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1 (15-ounce) jar roasted red peppers, rinsed and drained &QR;
</P>
<P>
   8 sun-dried tomato halves, soaked in hot water 5 minutes and
drained well &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1 garlic clove, minced &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1 to 2 tablespoons fresh lemon juice &QR;
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons chopped flat-leafed parsley &QR;
</P>
<P>
   4 ounces cream cheese, cut into bits and softened &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 to 2/3 cup dairy sour cream &QR;
</P>
<P>
   Salt and pepper to taste &QR;
</P>
<P>
   In a food processor, puree peppers, tomatoes, garlic, lemon
juice and parsley until as smooth as possible. Add remaining
ingredients; puree mixture until almost smooth. Serve with grilled
chicken breasts. Makes about 2 1/4 cups, 6 to 8 servings.
</P>
<P>
   (Adapted from a 1991 issue of Gourmet magazine.) &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
STRAWBERRY-MANGO SALSA &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1 pint basket (12 ounces) strawberries, rinsed, stemmed and
chopped &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1 large mango, peeled, seeded and chopped &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup sliced green onions with tops &QR;
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons fresh lime juice &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon chopped cilantro &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon red pepper flakes &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1/4 teaspoon ground cumin &QR;
</P>
<P>
   Salt to taste &QR;
</P>
<P>
   In a bowl, toss together all ingredients except salt; blend
thoroughly. Mix in salt. Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate
overnight. Serve with grilled chicken OR white fish or corn chips.
Makes about 3 cups. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
THAI TOMATO SALSA &QL; 
2 green onions, cleaned, 3 inches green left on and slivered
lengthwise &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup fresh lemon juice &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 large bunches cilantro, leaves removed and finely minced &QR;
</P>
<P>
   2 cloves garlic, peeled and finely minced &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup slivered fresh basil leaves &QR;
</P>
<P>
   4 ripe plum tomatoes, seeded and cut into 1/8-inch dice &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup peeled and diced purple onion (1/8-inch dice) &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 teaspoons peeled and grated fresh ginger root &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon balsamic vinegar &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1/4 to 1/3 cup olive oil &QR;
</P>
<P>
   Salt and pepper to taste &QR;
</P>
<P>
   In a small bowl, soak green onions in lemon juice 30 minutes.
Drain; reserve 1/2 of lemon juice. Mince green onions.
</P>
<P>
   In a medium bowl, combine green onions, reserved lemon juice and
remaining ingredients. Mix together well. Serve over grilled or
broiled fish or chicken. Makes enough for 6 to 8 servings. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
YOGURT CUCUMBER DILL SAUCE &QL; 
1 (8-ounce) carton plain low-fat yogurt &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1 to 2 tablespoons dry Ranch House dressing mix &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup peeled, seeded, chopped cucumber &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon dried dill weed (OR use a couple of tablespoons
fresh) &QR;
</P>
<P>
   Combine all ingredients in a small bowl, mixing well. Keep
refrigerated. Use sauce to top grilled fish or chicken or serve
with meat- or vegetable-filled pita sandwiches. Makes about 1 1/2
cups sauce. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
ANTIPASTO SALSA &QL; 
If you like the tangy bite of briny olives and marinated artichoke
hearts, you will enjoy this colorful melange of antipasto
favorites. &QL; 
1 cup chopped pimiento-stuffed green olives &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1 cup pitted, chopped Greek OR Italian black olives OR pitted
ripe olives &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1 cup chopped marinated artichoke hearts &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup chopped roasted red peppers &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup packed chopped fresh basil &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1 clove garlic, minced OR pressed &QR;
</P>
<P>
   3 tablespoons red wine vinegar &QR;
</P>
<P>
   Pepper to taste &QR;
</P>
<P>
   In a serving bowl, stir together all ingredients. Let stand 20
minutes to blend flavors. Served over grilled meats, fish or
poultry. Makes about 3 1/2 cups. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
WOLFGANG PUCK'S TOMATO BASIL VINAIGRETTE &QL; 
3 tablespoons chopped fresh basil &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup extra-virgin olive oil &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon lime juice &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon good red OR white wine vinegar &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon minced fresh parsley &QR;
</P>
<P>
   2 medium shallots, minced &QR;
</P>
<P>
   6 ripe plum tomatoes, peeled, seeded and diced &QR;
</P>
<P>
   2 cloves garlic, blanched and cut into julienne strips &QR;
</P>
<P>
   Salt and freshly ground pepper to taste &QR;
</P>
<P>
   In a bowl, combine all ingredients. Taste and correct
seasonings. Serve with grilled tuna, salmon or swordfish. Makes
enough for 4 servings.
</P>
<P>
   NOTE: For attractive presentation, nap 4 plates with vinaigrette
and top with one piece of grilled fish. Garnish with basil sprigs. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
BLACK OLIVE AND CITRUS RELISH &QL; 
2 oranges &QR;
</P>
<P>
   2 lemons &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup pitted black olives, chopped into small pieces &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1 small red onion, diced small &QR;
</P>
<P>
   3 green onions, chopped &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon ground cumin &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper &QR;
</P>
<P>
   Salt and freshly cracked black pepper to taste &QR;
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons chopped fresh parsley &QR;
</P>
<P>
   Peel oranges and lemons, separate into sections and remove outer
membranes and seeds.
</P>
<P>
   Put fruit into a medium bowl; add all remaining ingredients and
mix well. This will keep, covered and refrigerated, a day or two.
Serve with grilled meats or fish. Makes about 2 cups. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
AVOCADO AND CORN SALSA &QL; 
2 cups cooked corn kernels &QR;
</P>
<P>
   2 ripe avocados, peeled, pitted and diced &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1 red onion, finely diced &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1 red bell pepper, seeded and finely diced &QR;
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons olive oil &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup red wine vinegar &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon minced garlic &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon ground cumin &QR;
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup fresh lime juice (2 limes) &QR;
</P>
<P>
   Salt and coarsely ground black pepper to taste &QR;
</P>
<P>
   Place corn in a bowl; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Serve with grilled chicken. Salsa is best served immediately, but
it can be kept covered and refrigerated, up to 4 hours. Makes about
4 cups, 6 to 8 servings. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
