<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR TUESDAY, JULY 4 
</HEADLINE>
  (EDS: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Tuesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.) 
 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-MAGENER-NYT (sent on Sunday, July 2) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service obituary sent on Sunday, July 2
about Rolf Mageren, a German businessman who escaped a World War II
British internment camp in India disguised as an Englishman,
misstated the date of his death. It was May 5, not June 3.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BC-MEDIA-TALK-NYT (sent on Sunday, July 2) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, July 2
about criticism within NBC of the performance of Scott Sassa,
president of the NBC television network's West Coast division,
imprecisely summarized a portion of an article in The New York Post
about him last Friday. The Post article cited an unidentified
person as saying that Sassa might leave his job within days, and it
quoted an NBC spokeswoman as denying reports that Sassa had been
asked to resign. The Post article did not say conclusively that
Sassa would be out of his job within days.  &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BC-ECOMMERCE-COLUMN-NYT (sent on Sunday, July 2) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, July 2
about companies that enable consumers to review the personal data
that companies have collected about them misspelled the name of one
of the companies. It is the Acxiom Corp., not Axciom.  &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BC-CIR-WEB-SEARCH-NYT (sent on Wednesday, June 26) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, June 26
about efforts to improve Internet search engines misstated the
location of the NEC Corp., whose research division, the NEC
Research Institute, reported last summer on search engine problems.
NEC Corp.'s headquarters are in Tokyo, not Princeton, N.J.
</P>
</TEXT>
