 NAPSTER BEING BULLIED, LAWYER SAYS  &HT;     By BENNY EVANGELISTA 
 &HT;     c. 2000 The San Francisco Chronicle 
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ Napster Inc.'s high-powered lawyer, who was the
trust-busting attorney who led the government's prosecution of
Microsoft Corp., said Monday that the recording industry wants to
squash his client to maintain its tight control on record sales.
</P>
